The paper focuses on image retrieval tasks using hashing techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper leverages generative adversarial networks (GANs) for generating synthetic data, which is a popular topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of supervised information and the limitations of annotating data, which suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper evaluates its proposed method on image benchmarks, indicating that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel deep semantic hashing method, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
